0.name: 1Scientist Log
0.text:
Year 154, day 136.

Business as usual. 
Project nutcracker is well on the way. 
These droids are getting more advanced by the day. 
Especially since Geoffrey joined us a week ago. 
Great stuff. 
Me out.

1.name: 2Scientist Log
1.text:
Year 154, day 139.

Uhh giants are still as prevalent as allways. 
Uh. 
We started to experiment with emotional manipulation alongside project nutcracker. 
We just need the proper items to uh bind it to. 
Me out.

2.name: 3Scientist Log
2.text:
Year 154, day 146.

We used masks.. Big mistake. 
They seem to get stuck to their wearers.. 
uh.. 
No other side effects have been noted. 

I haven't seen it myself but I've heard project nutcracker was a succes! 
It sounds like they're actually alive! 
uh.. 
We also noticed that Geoffrey went missing recently. 
We are looking into that. 
Me out.

3.name: 4Scientist Log
3.text:
Year 154, day 15.. something.

I am on the run. 
Those masks.. took them. 
They're not them anymore. 
They took my team! Converted half of them! 
The nutcrackers are not droids like I thought. 
I.. I saw one of them. 
It shot me.. right in the chest before I got here. 
I'm bleeding out. 
I think the nutcrackers.. 
They're my coworkers.. 
Or what's left of them. 
I think those masked men.. 
I think they.. 

*Gunshot*

4.name: Protocol Wipeout
4.text:
Year 154, day 12.

Today is a scary day. 
Protocol wipeout was approved and the nuclear bomb will be installed tomorrow. 
Knowing where it came from I no longer feel quite as safe here. 
I can only imagine what could go wrong. 
Worse. 
How it could ruin years of research and experimentation! 
In case you don't know.. 
Protocol wipeout is only called during.. events of disaster. 
Destroying. 
Everything. 
As much as I am facinated with the craft, I refuse to let it destroy all we've done. 
Perhaps I could modify some of its components. 
We'll see. 
Now that project hawk is complete, we have received plans for new machines that will be used in the Grand War that just broke out. 
It will be called, Project Nutcracker. 
I'm excited. 
Me out.
